''For the hadith scholar '''Al-Zuhri''' see [[Ibn Shihab al-Zuhri]].''
'''Mohammed Ibn Abi Bakr al-Zuhri''' of [[Granada]] ([[floruit|fl.]] 1130s–1150s) was a geographer. He was the writer of a notable work, ''Kitab al-Jaghrafiyya'' (Book of Geography). Al-Zuhri was able to use the writings of the geographers of the reign of Caliph [[Al-Ma'mun]] of [[Baghdad]] (d. 456/1068).<ref>S. M. Imamuddin, ''Muslim Spain 711-1492 A.D.'', p. 159</ref> Al-Zuhri died between 1154 and 1161.
